      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BATCITY (7) wasn't far away here over 1300m on debut, beaten 2.5 lengths. Settled well back and raced wide after. Draws inside today and should enjoy a softer run. Big chance stepping up to 1600m. MR FRODO (2) improved at Scarpside and then came from well back, beaten just 1.4L over 1400m at Belmont at odds. Gives every indication that 1600m will suit and he has winning claims. RARE HONOR (1) switches back from a middle distance and should be better suited. Missed a whisker over 1800m at Scarpside three back and then placed distantly there the one following over this trip. Has a low draw and can do better. BHULLAR (8) went well, placing second at Scarpside over 1400m, but didn't manage the wide barrier here last time. Should get a soft run from the inside gate and will get every chance to run out the longer journey.",
